The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, July 19, 2004  Calcutta Column

	Examinees find it difficult to write fast because the bench or desk at the examination centre is often faulty. Those conducting the examinations should make necessary arrangements so that candidates do not face any discomfort. I had suffered while taking an exam in 1984. Years on, the situation is the same. Biman Saha, Lake Town. 
	The nine-day Rath mela on Rashbehari Avenue was held under pitiable conditions. The roads were dug up, stalls put up on both flanks and autos clogged the remaining space. How did the authorities permit the mela under the circumstances? Prantik Sanyal, SP Mukherjee Road. 
